        rationale: "Hydroxychloroquine is recommended for virtually all SLE patients because it reduces flares, prolongs survival, and has antithrombotic properties (inhibits platelet aggregation, reduces antiphospholipid antibody levels, improves endothelial function). These combined effects reduce both SLE disease activity and LSE progression."
