      right: ["Acute variceal hemorrhage: hematemesis, melena, hemodynamic instability (15-20% mortality)","Tense ascites with respiratory compromise requiring emergent paracentesis","SBP: fever, abdominal pain, worsening encephalopathy in ascites patient","Grade III-IV encephalopathy: stupor or coma requiring ICU","Hepatorenal syndrome type 1: rapidly progressive renal failure","MELD >=25: high short-term mortality; urgent transplant evaluation"]
